DZEN(1)                                        General Commands Manual                                        DZEN(1)

NNAAMMEE
       dzen2 - general-purpose messaging and notification for X11

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ddzzeenn22 [-v] [-p [seconds]] [-m [v|h]] [-ta <l|c|r>] [-sa <l|c|r>]
             [-x <pixel>] [-y <pixel>] [-w <pixel>] [-tw <pixel>] [-u]
             [-e <string>] [-l <lines>]  [-fn <font>] [-bg <color>]
             [-fg <color>] [-xs <screen>]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       DDzzeenn  is  a  general-purpose messaging and notification program for X11, desigend to be scriptable in any lan‐
       guage and integrate well with window managers like dwm, wmii and xmonad though it will work with  any  window‐
       manger.

       DDzzeenn  expects  the  status message on its standard input, and uses a custom formatting language for colors and
       several other features (like bar meters and such). See README for detailed usage and scripting instructions.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --ffgg <<ccoolloorr>>
              Set foreground color. The <color> can be specified either as symbolic name (e.g. red, darkgreen,  etc.)
              or as #rrggbb hex-value (e.g. #ffffaa).

       --bbgg <<ccoolloorr>>
              Set background color (same format as -fg).

       --ffnn <<ffoonntt>>
              Set font (using the format of xlsfonts and xfontsel).

       --ttaa <<ll||cc||rr>>
              Set alignement of title window content: l(eft), c(center) or r(ight).

       --ttww <<ppiixxeellss>>
              Set title window width.

       --ssaa <<ll||cc||rr>>
              Set alignment of slave window (see --ttaa ).

       --ll <<lliinneess>>
              Number of lines to display in slave window (see (1) in README).

       --ee <<eevveenntt11==aaccttiioonn11::ooppttiioonn11::......,,aaccttiioonn22;;eevveenntt22==......>>
              Set up events and actions, eg. responses to mouse clicks (see (2) in README).

       --mm     Start up in menu mode (see (3) in README).

       --uu     Update contents of title and slave window simultaneously, see (see (4) in README).

       --pp [[<<ttiimmeeoouutt>>]]
              Persist EOF (optional timeout in seconds).

       --xx <<ppiixxeellss>>
              Set x position on the screen.

       --yy <<ppiixxeellss>>
              Set y position on the screen.

       --hh <<ppiixxeellss>>
              Set line height (defaults to fontheight + 2 pixels).

       --ww <<ppiixxeellss>>
              width

       --xxss <<nn>>
              Set the Xinerama screen number where dzen should appear.

       --vv     Display version information.

AAUUTTHHOORR
       DDzzeenn22  has  been written by RRoobbeerrtt MMaanneeaa..  This manpage has been written, based on dzen documentation, by Petr
       Ročkai, for Debian GNU/Linux, but may be used by others. This manpage falls under the same  licence  as  Dzen2
       itself, see /usr/share/doc/dzen2/copyright.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       ddzzeenn22--ddbbaarr(1),  ddzzeenn22--ggccppuubbaarr(1),  ddzzeenn22--ggddbbaarr(1), and ddzzeenn22--tteexxttwwiiddtthh(1).  More detailed documentation (espe‐
       cially on the formatting language of dzen2) is available in /usr/share/doc/dzen2/README.gz.

